.TH NCI-ALL 1
.SH NAME
nci-all \- run npm ci in parallel across all package directories, then build selected packages.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nci-all

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B nci-all
function discovers all
.B package.json
directories up to 2 levels deep (via
.BR find-package-dirs (1))
and runs
.B npm ci --legacy-peer-deps
in each of them concurrently. Once all installs complete, it sequentially builds a predefined set of packages (currently
.B common
and
.BR mv-agent )
by running
.B npm run build
in those directories.

Progress and success/failure status is printed to the console for each package.

.SH OPTIONS
No options. The function takes no arguments.

.SH DEPENDENCIES
.IP \[bu] 2
.BR find-package-dirs (1)
\- must be sourced before this function.
.IP \[bu] 2
.B npm
\- must be installed and in the system's PATH.

.SH USAGE
From the root of a monorepo or workspace:
.B nci-all

.SH SEE ALSO
find-package-dirs(1), npm(1)

.SH AUTHOR
Ramo Mislimi (mislimi.ramo@gmail.com)
